INSERT INTO `xz_dialogue` VALUES (1415, 'Here\'s the Java code equivalent to the provided Python code:\n\n\n```java\nimport java.util.*;\n\npublic class Main {\n    static int[] dep;\n    static int[] sz;\n    static List<Integer>[] g;\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);\n        int n = scanner.nextInt();\n        int k = scanner.nextInt();\n\n        g = new List[n + 1];\n        dep = new int[n + 1];\n        sz = new int[n + 1];\n\n        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {\n            g[i] = new ArrayList<>();\n        }\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {\n            int a = scanner.nextInt();\n            int b = scanner.nextInt();\n            g[a].add(b);\n            g[b].add(a);\n        }\n\n        dfs(1, -1, 0);\n\n        Integer[] l = new Integer[n];\n        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {\n            l[i - 1] = sz[i] - dep[i];\n        }\n\n        Arrays.sort(l, Collections.reverseOrder());\n\n        long ans = 0;\n        for (int i = 0; i < n - k; i++) {\n            ans += l[i];\n        }\n\n        System.out.println(ans);\n    }\n\n    private static int dfs(int i, int fa, int d) {\n        int cnt = 1;\n        for (int nx : g[i]) {\n            if (nx != fa) {\n                cnt += dfs(nx, i, d + 1);\n            }\n        }\n        dep[i] = d;\n        sz[i] = cnt - 1;\n        return cnt;\n    }\n}\n```\nExplanation:\n\n1. We start by reading the input `n` and `k` from the console.\n2. We initialize the arrays `dep`, `sz`, and the adjacency list `g`.\n3. We read the edges of the tree and add them to the adjacency list.\n4. We call the `dfs` function to compute the depth (`dep`) and subtree size (`sz`) for each node.\n5. We create an array `l` to store the values `sz[i] - dep[i]` for each node.\n6. We sort the array `l` in descending order.\n7. We compute the answer by summing the first `n - k` elements of the sorted array `l`.\n8. Finally, we print the answer.\n\nNote: The Java code uses a `Scanner` for input and prints the output to the console. Make sure to compile and run the Java code using a Java compiler and runtime environment.', 174, 'assistant', '2024-04-27 01:05:45');
