INSERT INTO `xz_dialogue` VALUES (1643, 'Here\'s the C++ version of your updated Python code:\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n\nusing namespace std;\n\nconst int MAXN = 100;\nint row[MAXN];\nbool col[MAXN], p1[MAXN * 2], p2[MAXN * 2];\nint total = 0;\nint n;\n\nbool check(int i, int j) {\n    return !col[j] && !p1[i + j] && !p2[i - j + n];\n}\n\nvoid dfs(int i) {\n    if (i == n) {\n        total++;\n        if (total <= 3) {\n            for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {\n                cout << row[k] << \" \";\n            }\n            cout << endl;\n        }\n        return;\n    }\n\n    for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {\n        if (check(i, j)) {\n            row[i] = j + 1;\n            col[j] = true;\n            p1[i + j] = true;\n            p2[i - j + n] = true;\n            dfs(i + 1);\n            row[i] = 0;\n            col[j] = false;\n            p1[i + j] = false;\n            p2[i - j + n] = false;\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nint main() {\n    cin >> n;\n    dfs(0);\n    cout << total << endl;\n    return 0;\n}\n```\n\nIn this C++ code:\n\n- `row` is an integer array to store the column index (plus one, to match your Python code) where a queen is placed in each row.\n- `col`, `p1`, and `p2` are boolean arrays to keep track of occupied columns and diagonals, respectively.\n- The `check` function verifies if a position `(i, j)` is valid by checking columns and diagonals (rows are implicitly checked by the recursive structure of `dfs`).\n- The `dfs` function performs a depth-first search to find all valid solutions, placing queens row by row.\n- In the `main` function, the user inputs the size of the board `n`, and then `dfs` is called starting from row 0. Finally, the total number of solutions is printed.\n\nNote that in the C++ version, there is no need for a global `ans` list since we are only interested in printing the first three solutions and the total count. The solutions themselves are not stored explicitly; instead, they are printed as they are found during the recursive search.', 223, 'assistant', '2024-07-02 23:43:19');
